1.BASIC LINUX COMMANDS

pwd
Print Working Directory

ls
List Directory Contents
Examples
ls
ls -l
ls -lah /var/log

cd
Change Directory

clear
Clear Terminal Screen

history
Command History

which
Locate Executable Path
which kubectl

whoami
Current Logged-in User

2. FILE & DIRECTORY MANAGEMENT COMMANDS

touch
Create Empty File
touch file.txt

mkdir
Create Directory
mkdir mydir
mkdir -p parent/child

cp
Copy Files / Directories
cp source destination

mv
Move or Rename
mv oldname newname
mv file.txt /tmp/

rm
Remove Files / Directories
rm file.txt
rm -rf directory

cat
View File Content
cat file.txt

head
First Lines of File
head -n 10 file.txt

tail
Last Lines of File
tail -n 20 file.log

find
Search Files
find /var/log -name "*.log"

grep
Search Text Patterns
grep "ERROR" app.log

chmod
Change Permissions
chmod 755 script.sh
chmod +x script.sh

df
Disk Usage (Filesystem)
df -h

du
Directory Size
du -sh /var/log


3. USER & GROUP MANAGEMENT COMMANDS

useradd
Create User
useradd username
useradd -m username
-m creates home directory.

passwd
Set User Password
passwd username

usermod
Modify User
usermod -aG sudo username
Adds user to sudo group.

userdel
Delete User
userdel username
userdel -r username
-r removes home directory.

id
User ID and Group Info
id username

su
Switch User
su - username

sudo
Run Command as Root
sudo apt update

Important Files
File	Purpose
/etc/passwd	User details
/etc/shadow	Encrypted passwords
/etc/group	Group information

4. PROCESS & SYSTEM COMMANDS

ps
Running Processes
ps -ef

top
Real-time Process Monitor

htop
Enhanced Process Monitor

kill
Terminate Process
kill PID
kill -9 PID

uptime
System Run Time

free
Memory Usage
free -h

uname
System Information
uname -a
